# Spec-driven workflow

All meaningful work must be traceable to SDD, ADR, prompt, checklist, or task brief.

## Required behavior

- Use `docs/specs/SDD.md` as the canonical SDD entrypoint.
- Keep detailed SDD sections in `docs/sdd/`.
- Update ADRs when architecture, access, external services, dependencies, or policy decisions change.
- Keep prompt/rule changes aligned with the SDD and governance docs.
- Work in small, reversible diffs and document residual risks.

## Stop conditions

Stop and request human review when a task requires:

- new credentials or access to real systems;
- personal or sensitive data;
- production deploys or migrations;
- security/compliance policy changes;
- large refactors or mass deletions;
- new external services or dependencies.
